                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>96 Orange St.</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Kingston Jam</placeName>: <date>6<hi rend=\"sup\"\n                        >th</hi> March<lb/>1863</date>.</p>\n            <p>My dear <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I duly acknowledge<lb/> your last 2 letters, and the receipt of<lb/>\n                Occidents and 3 copies of the printed<lb/> Edition of the Pentateuch. You must<lb/>\n                like all good and loyal citizens of the<lb/> great Republic, submit to the\n                difficulties<lb/> of the present situation. When so much<lb/> paper is required for\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">Green Backs</hi> and<lb/> other numerous varieties of\n                notes, issued<lb/> for the maintenance of public credit, the<lb/> Editor of the\n                Occident should not grumble<lb/> at the rise in price of printing material.<lb/>\n                Sacrifices are indispensable on the part<lb/> of every individual when so glorious a\n                war<lb/> for the redemption and freedom of the negro<lb/> race, and the subjugation\n                of white rebels<lb/> is to be brought to a triumphant close.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
