                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>When that object is accomplished, your self<lb/> denial, tho' it may involve you in\n                pecuniary<lb/> losses, will be appreciated; and congress, when<lb/> personally\n                appealed to, will, doubtless, especially<lb/> the <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >republican</hi> part of it, recompense you with<lb/> a grant from the public\n                treasury. Your petition<lb/> cannot fail of being signed by all the Jewish<lb/>\n                population throughout the States, and public<lb/> virtue will thus meet its own\n                reward. I have<lb/> not yet had time to peruse the article to which<lb/> you direct\n                my attention. My time is so occupied<lb/> with my school, owing to the Shamash of\n                the<lb/> Congregation; my assistant Hebrew teacher,<lb/> having left for\n                    <placeName>California</placeName>, that I have had no<lb/> leisure. Our new\n                minister, <persName>Mr. Myers</persName>, has got<lb/> himself into a dilemma with\n                some of the big<lb/> wigs of the Synagogue, in consequence of his<lb/> many refusal\n                to sanction the calling up to<lb/> the Sepher, of people married to Christian\n                women,<lb/> and <hi rend=\"underline\">colored</hi> women to boot. You can have\n                no<lb/> conception of the falling off in this particular congre-<lb/>gation from\n                various causes within the last twenty<lb/> years. Its numerous members have dwindled\n                down<lb/> to a mere <sic>handfull</sic>; but the pride and arrogance<lb/> remain as\n                of old; and tincture all their acts, to<lb/> which had feelings, towards all who\n                venture to differ<lb/> from the <hi rend=\"underline\">rulers</hi> in opinion, largely\n                add their share.<lb/> As for the <hi rend=\"underline\">minister</hi> of the other\n                Synagogue, De<add>?</add><lb/> the least I say of him the better. I am not a\n                    <add>מלשין</add></p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
