                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"indent(1)\">work out for the Occident, if my <hi rend=\"underline\">liver</hi> permits.<lb/>\n                <persName>Moses</persName>, it is evident could not have imposed on the<lb/> 2\n                    <add>?</add> tribes the duty of going over the <placeName>Jordan</placeName>\n                <add>חמשים</add><lb/> but only <add>חלוצים</add> armed for war; and therefore he\n                uses the<lb/> latter; whereas <persName>Joshua</persName> could, as commanded,<lb/>\n                decline to forage for them, and compel them to manage<lb/> their own commissariat.\n                The sacred text is not<lb/> strained to <del>meet</del>\n                <sic>acord</sic> with this explanation but rather<lb/> removes the difficulty of\n                accounting in what<lb/> way the people subsisted, until the <add>?</add><lb/>\n                fell.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I have formed an acquaintance with<lb/> a <persName>Dr.\n                    Daniell</persName>—of the British army, a man<lb/> of wonderful knowledge in all\n                matters relating<lb/> to <placeName>Africa</placeName>, where he passed 18 years of\n                his life.<lb/> He is a great scholar, not alone in the studies<lb/> appertaining to\n                his profession, but in others, and<lb/> is esteemed an <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >authority</hi> in <placeName>England</placeName> in philology,<lb/> ethnology,\n                botany, &amp;c. A bosom friend of <persName>Professor<lb/> Owen</persName> the\n                Eminent naturalist. We had a<lb/> delightful evening's talk till 12 o'Clock\n                last<lb/> night, and that is how I spent my <date>Purim</date>. He<lb/> possesses\n                monotheism, but believes in the Bible,<lb/> not I think, in the Testament.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">The war, I see, continues to linger.<lb/> The termination cannot\n                however be very<lb/> distant, and I hope it will end as I wish.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/canvas/p3"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
