          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/canvas/p4/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>It may however become more complicated<lb/> by the defiant attitude of one of\n                the<lb/> belligerents towards the French Emperor.<lb/> The English Government is not\n                hypocritical.<lb/> Your charge is not just. If it had intervened,<lb/> I incline to\n                think with <persName>Lords Palmerston</persName><lb/> and\n                    <persName>Russel</persName> that the <placeName>north</placeName> would have\n                raised<lb/> such an overwhelming force as would have<lb/> crushed the\n                    <placeName>south</placeName> at once <add>אל תעמוד לפני רעך בשעת כעסו</add><lb/>\n                applies as well to nations as individuals.<lb/>\n                <placeName>England</placeName> has enough on her hands in meeting the<lb/> hungry\n                cravings of her starving operatives<lb/> without putting her fingers into her\n                neighbour's<lb/> dish. I call their neutral action wise and<lb/> humane, and it will\n                prove to be so in the<lb/> long run. The feelings of the English government<lb/>\n                &amp; nation too are with the <placeName>south</placeName>, and the<lb/> ravings of\n                    <persName>Bright</persName> &amp; <persName>Cobden</persName> and the anti-<lb/>\n                slavery party are ineffectual to change them.<lb/> I am alive to the short comings\n                of my native<lb/> country, but <del>they are</del> in this matter it is not<lb/>\n                obnoxious to the abuse lavished upon it by the<lb/> people of\n                    <placeName>America</placeName>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">My wife and mother join with<lb/> me in affectionate wishes &amp;\n                regards</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">Yours Sincerely</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(8)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">M N Nathan</persName>\n            </p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/canvas/p4"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
