              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/manifest/annotation/p5",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>but I would surprise you, were I to often the<lb/> budget of doings and sayings of\n                this man. Judaism<lb/> is in a bad state here, spirit of religion is utterly<lb/>\n                wanting, with no one competent to rouse it from the<lb/> torpor into which it has\n                fallen. We have had here a<lb/> certain <persName>Rabbi Alfendri</persName> from\n                    <placeName>Smyrna</placeName>, his mission<lb/> here was a failure; we are too\n                poor ourselves, and<lb/> have too many indigent ones in our midst, to<lb/>\n                contribute to the claims (?) of such travelling gentry.<lb/> Why don't they stop at\n                home? We hear of the<lb/> doings and writings of <persName>Mr. De Solla</persName>,\n                late of <placeName>Montego<lb/> Bay</placeName>, against <persName>Mr.\n                    Morais</persName>. Can't you send me some<lb/> of that precious productions? Are\n                you not going<lb/> to use your pen in defense of scripture against<lb/>\n                <persName>Bishop Calendo</persName>? <persName>Benisch</persName> has come out\n                manfully,<lb/> but altho' he has answered some points admirably,<lb/> I do not like\n                    <hi rend=\"underline\">all</hi> he has written. The wood, water,<lb/> and pasture\n                question he has handled ably. I<lb/> am, just to keep my hand in, maintaining a\n                cor<lb/>respondence on the subject with a <sic>xtian</sic> clergyman;<lb/> and made\n                the word <add>חמשים</add>\n                <del>the</del> my study, at his request.<lb/> I cannot agree that it means equipped,\n                or harnessed,<lb/> in gist, or armed, but <add>?</add> think it signifies<lb/> v<hi\n                    rend=\"underline\">ictualled</hi> or <hi rend=\"underline\">provisioned</hi> from\n                    <add>חמץ</add> the abdomen.<lb/> The Bible says <add>וגם צדה לא עשו להם</add>;\n                Does that imply that<lb/> they had no <hi rend=\"underline\">food</hi> at all except\n                the <add>בצק</add>? I should say<lb/> that <add>צדה</add> means <hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >cooked</hi> or <hi rend=\"underline\">prepared</hi> provisions, and<lb/>\n                <add>עשו</add> being joined to it, an act of preparation or<lb/> cooking is\n                inferred, the same as <add>אפה</add> to <add>בצק</add> before<lb/> the latter\n                becomes <add>לחם</add>. Hence the Israelites might</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hd7pd03/canvas/p5"
