               the objections of<lb/> those who assert that the people had no food but<lb/> the\n                    <add>בצק</add>. God did not lead them thro' a fertile country<lb/> like the\n                    <add>ארץ פלשתים</add>, but into the <add>מדבר</add>; yet that unpro-<lb/>ductive\n                waste had no terrors for them, they had no<lb/> immediate fears of hunger, for they\n                were <add>חמשים</add> furnished<lb/> with food, tho' not with <add>צדה</add> cooked\n                food. If<lb/> rationalists must be satisfied and shown demon-<lb/>stratively that\n                the multitude was not in a<lb/> starving condition, my exegesis will convince<lb/>\n                them. This hasty sketch I may possibly</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
